<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute ja avalike teenistujate (edaspidi t&ouml;&ouml;taja) t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja kestuse ning korralduse alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the duration of and bases for the organisation of working and rest time of persons working on the basis of employment contracts, and of public servants (hereinafter employees). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaeg on reguleeritud muu seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not apply to employees whose working and rest time is regulated by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvid 7-9, 11-16 ja 19-21 v&otilde;ib j&auml;tta kohaldamata t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Implementation of &sect;&sect; 7-9, 11-16 and 19-21 of this Act is not mandatory with regard to employees who: </inglise>
<eesti>1) omavad iseseisvat otsustusp&auml;devust ning vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingule v&otilde;i ametiasutuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusele m&auml;&auml;ratlevad ise oma t&ouml;&ouml;aja, kusjuures nende t&ouml;&ouml;aega ei m&auml;&auml;ratleta otseselt ega kaudselt t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsuse v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) have independent decision-making powers and determine their working time themselves pursuant to their employment contracts or the statutes of the administrative agency, and their working time is not directly or indirectly determined by unilateral decision of the employers or agreement between the parties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) viivad kiriklikes &uuml;hendustes l&auml;bi usulisi talitusi ja teenistusi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) conduct religious services in religious associations. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 loetletud isikutele kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu &uuml;ldisi n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) General requirements concerning safety and health protection at work apply to the persons listed in subsections (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 toodud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kohta eraldi arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Employers are required to maintain separate records concerning the employees set out in subsection (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;aeg on seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud aeg, mille kestel t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid, alludes t&ouml;&ouml;andja juhtimisele ja kontrollile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Working time is time during which an employee is required to perform his or her duties in subordination to the management and supervision of the employer and which is determined in Acts, other legislation, a collective agreement, employment contract or agreement between the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkeaeg on aeg, mis ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rest time is time which is not working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm on seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arv mingis kalendriajavahemikus (p&auml;ev, n&auml;dal, kuu v&otilde;i muu ajavahemik). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The standard for working time is the number of working hours determined in Acts, other legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract during a certain period of calendar time (day, week, month or other period of time). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;ev on ajavahemik &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A working day is the period of time during a twenty-four hour period when an employee is required to perform his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;vahetus on ajavahemik, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A working shift is the period of time in shift work during which an employee is required to perform his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vahetus v&otilde;ib alata &uuml;hel ja l&otilde;ppeda teisel &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>A working shift can begin during one twenty-four hour period and end during the next twenty-four hour period. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dal on ajavahemik n&auml;dalas, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A working week is the period of time during a week during which an employee is required to perform his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja l&uuml;hendamine ja puhkeaja pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reduction of working time and extension of rest time </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i muu &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;aega v&otilde;ib l&uuml;hendada ja puhkeaega pikendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega, kui sellega ei kaasne palga v&auml;henemine ega muude palgatingimuste halvenemine. </eesti>
<inglise>Working time established for employees by law or other legislation may be reduced and rest time may be extended by a collective agreement or employment contract or unilateral decision of the employer unless this results in a reduction of wages or deterioration of other wage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of Working Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldine riiklik norm </eesti>
<inglise>General national standard for working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldine riiklik norm on 8 tundi p&auml;evas ehk 40 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The general national standard for working time of employees is eight hours per day or forty hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral l&auml;htutakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestamisel t&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldisest riiklikust normist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the recording of total working time, the recording of working time shall be based on the general national standard for working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>L&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Reduced working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aeg on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Reduced working time is: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 13-14-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - 4 tundi p&auml;evas ehk 20 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) four hours per day or twenty hours per week for employees who are 13-14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 15-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - 6 tundi p&auml;evas ehk 30 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) six hours per day or thirty hours per week for employees who are 15 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 16-17-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - 7 tundi p&auml;evas ehk 35 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>3) seven hours per week or thirty-five hours per week for employees who are 16-17 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del, tervistkahjustavatel ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;del - kuni 7 tundi p&auml;evas ehk kuni 35 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>4) seven hours per day or thirty-five hours per week for employees who perform underground work, work that poses a health hazard or work of a special nature; </inglise>
<eesti>5) koolide ja muude lasteasutuste &otilde;petajatel, kasvatajatel ja teistel &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatusalal t&ouml;&ouml;tavatel isikutel - kuni 7 tundi p&auml;evas ehk kuni 35 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>5) seven hours per day or thirty-five hours per week for teachers and educators working in schools and other child care institutions, and other persons working in the area of education. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) 13-14-aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada ainult koolivaheajal v&otilde;i osalemise korral etendusasutuste loomingulises tegevuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees who are 13-14 years of age may be required to work only during school holidays or in the case of participation in the artistic activities of performing arts institutions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) 13-17-aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada, arvestades k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-3 ja l&otilde;ikes 2 toodud t&ouml;&ouml;ajapiiranguid tingimusel, et t&ouml;&ouml; ei kahjusta t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervist, arengut ega takista osalemist &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;s. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employees who are 13-17 years of age may be required to work, taking into account the restrictions on working time set out in clauses 1) -3) and subsection (2) of this Act and on condition that the work does not harm the health or interfere with the development or studies of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Allmaat&ouml;&ouml;l, tervistkahjustaval ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;l l&uuml;hendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;aega, kui nad t&ouml;&ouml;tavad neis tingimustes v&auml;hemalt 30 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Working time of employees engaged in underground work, work which poses a health hazard or work of a special nature is reduced if they work under such conditions for at least thirty hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 nimetatud allmaat&ouml;&ouml;de, tervistkahjustavate ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;de ja punktis 5 nimetatud ametikohtade loetelu ning l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestuse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic shall establish a list of underground work, work that poses a health hazard and work of a special nature specified in clause (1) 4) of this section, the positions specified in clause 5) of this section and the duration of reduced working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Part-time working time </inglise>
<eesti>Osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg on t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormist l&uuml;hem t&ouml;&ouml;aeg, mida rakendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>Part-time working time is working time determined by an employer which is shorter than the established standard for working time and which is applied by agreement between an employee and the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; on t&ouml;&ouml;tamine &uuml;le kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Overtime is work which exceeds the agreed standard for working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral on &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ks arvestusperioodi t&ouml;&ouml;tundide &uuml;ldarvu &uuml;letavad t&ouml;&ouml;tunnid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the recording of total working time, overtime is the working hours which exceed the total number of working hours in a recording period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;ib teha poolte kokkuleppel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Overtime is permitted by agreement between the parties except in the cases specified in subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppele mittej&otilde;udmine ei tohi kahjustada otseselt ega kaudselt t&ouml;&ouml;taja olukorda. </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to reach an agreement shall have no direct or indirect adverse effect on the employee's situation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u korral on t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldust teha &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d, kui selline t&ouml;&ouml; on ajutine ja tuleb teha viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of force majeure, an employee is required to comply with an order of an employer to work overtime if such work is temporary and has to be performed promptly. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vahetust&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le ilmumata j&auml;&auml;mise korral, kui t&ouml;&ouml;s ei v&otilde;i tekkida vaheaega, on t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud teatama sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ja j&auml;tkama t&ouml;&ouml;d kui &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d, kuid mitte kauem kui neli tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a shift worker fails to come to work and the work cannot be discontinued, other employees are required to notify the employer thereof and continue the work as overtime, however not longer than for four hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; arvestust iga t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja iga &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; juhu kohta eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Employers are required to maintain separate records of overtime concerning every employee and every case of overtime. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restriction on overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le on keelatud rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall not be required to work overtime: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kellele see on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work overtime by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikut, kes kasvatab alla 12-aastast v&otilde;i puudega last v&otilde;i hooldab t&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetut isikut, v&otilde;ib rakendada &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 4 etten&auml;htud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person raising a child under twelve years of age or a disabled child, or a person taking care of a person with total incapacity for work may only be required to work overtime with his or her consent, except in the case prescribed in subsection 7 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnormid </eesti>
<inglise>Standard limits on overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koos &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ga ei v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;aeg n&auml;dalas &uuml;letada keskmiselt 48 tundi neljakuulise arvestusperioodi jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Working time together with overtime shall not exceed an average of forty-eight hours per week during a four-month recording period. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajat ei ole lubatud rakendada &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le nelja tunni p&auml;evas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees shall not be required to work overtime for more than four hours per day. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetuse kestus koos &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ga ei tohi &uuml;letada 12 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a shift together overtime shall not exceed twelve hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnorme ei rakendata v&auml;&auml;ramatust j&otilde;ust tingitud vajaduse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Standard limits on overtime are not applied in case of need arising from force majeure. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirnorme v&otilde;ib &uuml;letada: </eesti>
<inglise>The standard limits may be exceeded: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loodus&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i tootmisavarii ennetamiseks v&otilde;i nende tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for the prevention of a natural disaster or industrial accident or the expeditious elimination of the consequences thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi, t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku, t&ouml;&ouml;andja asjade h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i riknemise &auml;rahoidmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the prevention of an accident, work stoppage, or destruction of or damage to the property of the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja asendamiseks k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 etten&auml;htud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the replacement of an employee who is temporarily absent in the cases prescribed in clauses 1) and 2) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the cases provided for in subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib tema n&otilde;usolekul rakendada t&auml;iendavalt &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le 200 tunni ulatuses aastas j&auml;rgmistel tingimustel: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee may be required to work overtime with his or her consent to the extent of 200 additional hours per year on the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei n&otilde;ua t&ouml;&ouml;tajatelt vastavate kokkulepete s&otilde;lmimist ja t&auml;iendavast &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;st keeldumine ei kahjusta otseselt ega kaudselt t&ouml;&ouml;taja olukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the employer does not require the employees to enter into corresponding agreements with the employer and the employee's refusal to perform additional overtime work has no direct or indirect adverse effect on his or her situation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&auml;iendava &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemine ei tekita &uuml;lev&auml;simust ega kahjusta t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the performance of additional overtime work does not cause exhaustion or damage the employee's health; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;andja peab sellise t&ouml;&ouml; tegijate &uuml;le eraldi arvestust ja esitab vastava arvestuse t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorile ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindavale organisatsioonile nende n&otilde;udmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) employers are required to maintain separate records concerning the employees performing such work and submit the corresponding records to the labour inspectors of the location (residence) of the employers and to organisations which represent employees, at the request of the inspectors and organisations; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus keelduda t&auml;iendava &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemisest ning t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus t&auml;iendavat &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d keelata v&otilde;i piirata, kui k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 loetletud tingimusi v&otilde;i &uuml;ldiseid t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu n&otilde;udeid ei t&auml;ideta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) an employee has the right to refuse to perform additional overtime work and the labour inspector of the location (residence) of an employer has the right to prohibit or restrict additional overtime work if the conditions listed in clauses 1) -3) of this subsection or general requirements concerning safety and health protection at work are not complied with. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveaeg </eesti>
<inglise>On call time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valveaeg on osa puhkeajast, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja peab olema t&ouml;&ouml;andjale k&auml;ttesaadav erakorraliste t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On call time is part of rest time during which an employee must be available to the employee for the performance of extraordinary duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valveaja v&otilde;ib kehtestada lisaks t&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldisele kestusele, kui see on vajalik etten&auml;gematute ja edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On call time may be established in addition to the duration of the general working time if this is necessary to perform work of unforeseeable and urgent nature. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valveaja kestus on kuni 30 tundi kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of on call time is up to thirty hours per month. </inglise>
<eesti>Neid tunde ei arvata t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka ning nende eest maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja lisatasu. </eesti>
<inglise>On call hours are not included in working time and the employer shall pay additional remuneration for on call time. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valveaja kestus, rakendamise kord ja lisatasu suurus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The duration of and procedure for application of on call time, and the amount of additional remuneration shall be determined by a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tamine &otilde;htusel ja &ouml;&ouml;ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Work during evening or night time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;htune aeg on ajavahemik kella 18.00-st - 22.00-ni, &ouml;&ouml;aeg on ajavahemik kella 22.00-st - 6.00-ni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Evening time is the time between 18.00 and 22.00 and night time is the time between 22.00 and 6.00. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;htusel ajal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada 13-14-aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tajat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees who are 13-14 years of age shall not be required to work during evening time. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Ouml;&ouml;ajal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following shall not be required to work during night time: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kellele see on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work during night time by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikut, kes kasvatab alla 12-aastast v&otilde;i puudega last v&otilde;i hooldab t&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetut isikut, v&otilde;ib rakendada t&ouml;&ouml;le &ouml;&ouml;ajal &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person raising a child under twelve years of age or a disabled child, or a person taking care of a person with total incapacity for work may be required to work during night time only with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;ldise t&ouml;&ouml;aja rakendamisel l&uuml;hendatakse vahetuse kestust &ouml;&ouml;ajal &uuml;he tunni v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the application of general working time, the duration of a shift shall be reduced by one hour during night time. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetuse kestuse l&uuml;hendamisel v&auml;heneb vastavalt ka t&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of the reduction of the duration of a shift, the duration of the standard for working time is also correspondingly reduced. </inglise>
<eesti>&Ouml;ise vahetuse kestus v&otilde;rdsustatakse p&auml;evasega, kui see on v&auml;ltimatu tootmistingimuste t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a night time shift can be made equal to a day time shift if this is unavoidable due to production conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) 13-14-aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib &otilde;htusel ajal ja 13-17-aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tajat &ouml;&ouml;ajal kuni kella 23.00-ni t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada t&ouml;&ouml;andaja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori loal juhul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaleb etendusasutuse loomingulises tegevuses tingimusel, et nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml; ei kahjusta t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervist, arengut ega takista osalemist &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;s. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An employee who is 13-14 years of age may be required to work during evening time and an employee who is 13-17 years of age may be required to work during night time until 23.00 with the permission of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer in the case the employee participates in the artistic activities of a performing arts institution, and on condition that the work does not harm the health or interfere with the development or studies of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja korraldus ja arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation and Recording of Working Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajakorraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Working time regime </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajakorralduse, see on t&ouml;&ouml;aja alguse ja l&otilde;pu, puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antava aja, samuti muud t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evasisesed vaheajad ning &uuml;hest vahetusest teise &uuml;lemineku aeg ja kord m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade v&otilde;i ametiasutuse sisekorraeeskirjaga, vahetuste ajakava, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>Working time regime, i.e. the beginning and end of working time, the time granted for rest and meals, other breaks during a working day, and the time and procedure for alternating shifts shall be determined in internal work procedure rules, internal procedure rules of an administrative agency, shift schedules, collective agreement or employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja jaotamine osadeks </eesti>
<inglise>Division of daily working time into parts </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;del, kus see on vajalik t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu t&otilde;ttu, v&otilde;ib kollektiivlepinguga v&otilde;i kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga jagada igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja osadeks, kusjuures vaheaeg v&otilde;ib &uuml;letada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud vaheaja kestust. </eesti>
<inglise>Working time may be divided into parts by a collective agreement or agreement with the employees where this is necessary due to the nature of the work; in such case the duration of breaks may exceed the duration of the break prescribed in subsection 16 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajaarvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Recording of working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama k&otilde;igi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers are required to maintain records of working time concerning all employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ajavahemik, mille jooksul t&auml;idetakse seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi, lepitakse kokku t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjades v&otilde;i ametiasutuse sisekorraeeskirjas, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The period of time during which standard for working time determined by an Act, other legislation, employment contract or collective agreement is used shall be determined by internal work procedure rules, internal procedure rules of an administrative agency, collective agreement or employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi t&auml;idetakse t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evast pikema ajavahemiku jooksul, kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case where standard for working time is used during a period longer than a working day, recording of total working time shall be applied. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui arvestusperioodiks on neljast kuust pikem ajavahemik, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeerimise tingimused koosk&otilde;lastama oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the recording period is a period of time longer than four months, an employer is required to co-ordinate the conditions for the totalling of working time with the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud koostama t&ouml;&ouml;ajakava kogu arvestusperioodi v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt iga kalendrikuu kohta ning tegema selle t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele teatavaks hiljemalt viis p&auml;eva enne arvestusperioodi v&otilde;i kalendrikuu algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon recording total working time, an employer is required to prepare a working time schedule for the entire recording period or at least for each calendar month and notify employees thereof not later than five days before the beginning of the recording period or calendar month. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus summeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestuse korral </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of daily working time in case of recording of total working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Summeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestuse korral v&otilde;ib vahetus kesta kuni 12 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the recording of total working time, the duration of a shift may be up to twelve hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Summeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestuse korral v&otilde;ib igap&auml;evane t&ouml;&ouml;aeg kesta: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of the recording of total working time, the duration of daily working time may be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 13-14-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel - kuni 5 tundi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) up to five hours for employees who are 13-14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 15-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel - kuni 7 tundi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) up to seven hours for employees who are 15 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 16-17-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel - kuni 8 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>3) up to eight hours for employees who are 16-17 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;ib kohaldada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatust suurema t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arvuga vahetust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Longer shifts than those provided for in subsection (1) of this section may be applied with the approval of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Rest Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaheaeg puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Breaks for rest and meals </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale andma vaheaja puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks p&auml;rast neli tundi kestnud t&ouml;&ouml;tamist, kui kollektiivlepingus ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to grant an employee a break for rest and meals after four hours of work unless otherwise provided for in the collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vaheaeg puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks kestab 30 minutist kuni 1 tunnini. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of a break for rest and meals shall be between thirty minutes and one hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks etten&auml;htud vaheajal on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;andja territooriumilt lahkuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee has the right to leave the premises of the employer during a break for rest and meals. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus v&otilde;ib teisiti kokku leppida juhul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja territooriumil on tagatud tingimused toitlustamiseks ja puhkamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>A different arrangement may be determined in a collective agreement or employment contract if conditions for taking meals and for resting are provided in the premises of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;del, kus t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu t&otilde;ttu pole v&otilde;imalik anda vaheaega puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks, luuakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imalus einetada t&ouml;&ouml;ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of work where it is not possible to grant breaks for rest and meals due to the nature of the work, employees shall be provided with an opportunity to take meals during working time. </inglise>
<eesti>Einetamise aeg arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>The time for taking a meal shall be included in working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaba aeg s&uuml;nnituseelseks l&auml;bivaatuseks </eesti>
<inglise>Free time for ante-natal examination </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud andma rasedale arsti otsuses n&auml;idatud ajal vaba aega s&uuml;nnituseelseks l&auml;bivaatuseks, mis arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is required to grant a pregnant woman free time for ante-natal examination on the time indicated in a decision of a doctor, and such time shall be included in working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaheajad lapse toitmiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Breaks for feeding child </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikule, kes kasvatab alla poolteiseaastast last, antakse peale &uuml;ldise vaheaja puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks lisavaheaegu lapse toitmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person raising a child under one and one half years of age shall be granted additional breaks for feeding the child in addition to the general breaks for rest and meals. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud lisavaheaeg antakse iga kolme tunni j&auml;rel kestusega iga kord mitte alla 30 minuti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The additional break specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be granted at least every three hours with a duration of not less than thirty minutes every time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahe v&otilde;i enama kuni poolteiseaastase lapse toitmiseks antava vaheaja kestus peab olema v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks tund. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a break granted for feeding two or more children of up to one and one half years of age shall be at least one hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isiku soovil liidetakse lapse toitmiseks etten&auml;htud vaheajad puhkamise ning einetamise vaheajaga v&otilde;i l&uuml;hendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva vastava ajavahemiku v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person so requests, the breaks prescribed for feeding a child shall be added to the breaks for rest and meals, or the working day shall be reduced by the corresponding period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vaheajad lapse toitmiseks arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka ja nende eest s&auml;ilitatakse keskmine palk riigieelarve vahenditest Sotsiaalministeeriumi eelarve kaudu sotsiaalministri kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Breaks for feeding a child are included in working time and payment of average wages shall be continued for the breaks from state budget funds through the budget of the Ministry of Social Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Muud t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evasisesed vaheajad </eesti>
<inglise>Other breaks during working day </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiivlepingu, vahetuste ajakava v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva v&otilde;i vahetuse jooksul lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 16, 17 ja 18 kehtestatud vaheaegadele ette n&auml;ha muid vaheaegu, mis arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition to the breaks established in &sect;&sect; 16, 17 and 18 of this Act, other breaks which are included in working time may be prescribed during a working day or shift by law, other legislation, in a collective agreement, shift schedule or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Igap&auml;evane puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Daily rest time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale antakse igap&auml;evast puhkeaega v&auml;hemalt 11 j&auml;rjestikust tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall be granted at least eleven consecutive hours of daily rest time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igap&auml;evase puhkeaja kestus on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of daily rest time is: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 13-14-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - v&auml;hemalt 18 j&auml;rjestikust tundi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at least eighteen consecutive hours for employees who are 13-14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 15-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - v&auml;hemalt 16 j&auml;rjestikust tundi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) at least sixteen consecutive hours for employees who are 15 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 16-17-aastasel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal - v&auml;hemalt 15 j&auml;rjestikust tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>3) at least fifteen consecutive hours for employees who are 16-17 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatust v&otilde;ib teha erandeid t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral seaduse v&otilde;i seaduse alusel v&auml;ljaantud muu &otilde;igusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of the recording of total working time, exceptions to subsection (1) of this section may be made by an Act or other legislation or collective agreement established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Igan&auml;dalane puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Weekly rest period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on v&auml;hemalt kaks puhkep&auml;eva n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees shall have at least two days off per week. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldised puhkep&auml;evad on laup&auml;ev ja p&uuml;hap&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>Standard days off are Saturday and Sunday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui katkestamatu t&ouml;&ouml;protsessi v&otilde;i elanike teenindamise vajaduse t&otilde;ttu laup&auml;eval ja p&uuml;hap&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;tatakse, antakse puhkep&auml;evad muudel &uuml;ksteisele j&auml;rgnevatel n&auml;dalap&auml;evadel ja need n&auml;hakse ette kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i vahetuste ajakavaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If work is done on Saturday and Sunday due to uninterrupted production process or a need to provide services to residents, days off shall be granted on other consecutive weekdays, and the days off shall be prescribed in employment contracts, collective agreements or shift schedules. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral on igan&auml;dalase puhkeaja kestus v&auml;hemalt 36 j&auml;rjestikust tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the recording of total working time, the duration of weekly rest time shall be at least thirty-six consecutive hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatust v&otilde;ib teha erandeid t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul, kusjuures igan&auml;dalase puhkeaja kestus on v&auml;hemalt 24 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Exceptions to subsections (2) and (3) of this section may be made with the agreement of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer; in such case the duration of weekly rest time shall be at least twenty four hours. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine puhkep&auml;eval </eesti>
<inglise>Requiring employees to work on days off </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;ib puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada tema n&otilde;usolekul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees may be required to work on days off with their consent, except in the cases prescribed in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldusel puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;le tulema ajutiste edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks v&auml;&auml;ramatust j&otilde;ust tingitud vajaduse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee is required to work on days off to perform temporary and urgent work in the case of need arising from force majeure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkep&auml;eval on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following shall not be required to work on days off: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kelle selline t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work on days off by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikut, kes kasvatab alla 12-aastast v&otilde;i puudega last v&otilde;i hooldab t&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetut isikut, v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud juhul puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person raising a child under twelve years of age or a disabled child, or a person taking care of a person with total incapacity for work may only be required to work on a day off in the cases prescribed in subsection (2) of this section with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Puudega lapse vanema, eestkostja ja hooldaja t&auml;iendav tasuline puhkep&auml;ev </eesti>
<inglise>Additional day off with pay for parent, guardian or curator of disabled child </inglise>
<eesti>Puudega lapse &uuml;hel vanematest, eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud sotsiaalhoolekande seaduse (RT I 1995, 21, 323; RT I 2001, 98, 617) &sect; 15 alusel kirjalik perekonnas hooldamise leping, on &otilde;igus saada lapse kasvatamiseks &uuml;ks lisapuhkep&auml;ev kuus, mille eest tasutakse keskmise palga alusel riigieelarve vahenditest Sotsiaalministeeriumi eelarve kaudu sotsiaalministri kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>One parent, guardian or a curator of a disabled child with respect to whom a written foster care contract has been entered into pursuant to &sect; 15 of the Social Welfare Act (RT I 1995, 21, 323; RT I 2001, 98, 617) has the right to an additional day off per month for raising the child, for which remuneration based on the average salary is paid from state budget funds through the budget of the Ministry of Social Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Doonoriks oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt &auml;ralubamine </eesti>
<inglise>Allowing employees who are blood donors to be absent from work </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud lubama doonoriks oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt &auml;ra vere andmise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers are required to allow employees who are blood donors to be absent from work on the day that blood is given. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva l&uuml;hendamine rahvusp&uuml;hale ja riigip&uuml;hale eelneval p&auml;eval </eesti>
<inglise>Reduction of working day on days preceding national holidays and public holidays </inglise>
<eesti>Uusaastale, Eesti Vabariigi aastap&auml;evale, v&otilde;idup&uuml;hale ja esimesele j&otilde;ulup&uuml;hale vahetult eelnevat t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva l&uuml;hendatakse kolme tunni v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>The working day directly preceding New Year's Day, Anniversary of the Republic of Estonia, Victory Day and Christmas Day is reduced by three hours. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine rahvusp&uuml;hal ja riigip&uuml;hal </eesti>
<inglise>Requiring employees to work on national or public holidays </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;tajat t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada rahvusp&uuml;hal ja riigip&uuml;hal, kui see on vajalik elanike teenindamiseks, katkematu t&ouml;&ouml;protsessi v&otilde;i ajutiste edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks v&auml;&auml;ramatust j&otilde;ust tingitud vajaduse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers may require employees to work on national or public holidays if this is necessary to provide services to the public, ensure uninterrupted production process, or to perform temporary and urgent work in the case of need arising from force majeure. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State supervision over compliance with this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof shall be exercised by the Labour Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise korral ja kontrollida ettekirjutuste t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, labour inspectors of the location (residence) of employers have the right to issue precepts and inspect compliance with the precepts. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutused on t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts issued by labour inspectors are mandatory for employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus kohaldada riiklikku sundi seadusega etten&auml;htud alusel ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Labour inspectors of the location (residence) of employers have the right to apply enforcement by the state on the basis and to the extent prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori otsuse tegemise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term for making decisions by labour inspectors </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor teeb k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud otsused ja teatab nendest taotlejale kirjaliku taotluse esitamisest arvates &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>Labour inspectors of the location (residence) of employers shall make the decisions prescribed by this Act and inform the applicants thereof within one week after the submission of a written application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutuse vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Contestation of precept of labour inspector </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei n&otilde;ustu oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusega, on tal &otilde;igus esitada T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajale kaebus ettekirjutuse saamisest arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer does not agree with a precept issued by a labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer, the employer has the right to file a complaint with the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate within ten calendar days after receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse esitamine ei vabasta kohustusest ettekirjutust t&auml;ita. </eesti>
<inglise>The filing of a complaint shall not release the person from the duty to comply with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi ning teeb oma otsuse, kas j&auml;tta ettekirjutus j&otilde;usse, see muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada, kaebuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate shall review the complaint and make a decision, within one week after the date of receipt of the complaint, on whether the precept remains in force, is amended or revoked. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse kaebuse esitajale teatavaks ning antakse k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>The person who filed the appeal or objection shall be notified of the decision, which shall be delivered to the person against a signature or sent by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaebaja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhtaja otsusega ei n&otilde;ustu, v&otilde;ib ta selle vaidlustada halduskohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the complainant does not agree with the decision of the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate, the complainant may file an appeal against with it in an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kaebuse esitamine halduskohtule ei v&otilde;ta t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt kohustust t&auml;ita oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutust kuni ettekirjutuse osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult seadusevastaseks tunnistava halduskohtulahendi j&otilde;ustumiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Filing of a complaint with an administrative court does not release an employer from the duty to comply with a precept issued by a labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer until the time that a judgment of the administrative court declaring the precept to be unlawful in its entirety or in part enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
