<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 31 j&otilde;ustub 2002. aasta 1. septembrist j&auml;rgmiste &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatusalal t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute suhtes: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Section 31 of this Act enters into force on 1 September 2002 regarding the following persons employed in the field of schooling and education: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lasteaed-algkooli, algkooli, p&otilde;hikooli, g&uuml;mnaasiumi (sealhulgas g&uuml;mnaasiumi, mille juures on p&otilde;hikooli klasse, ning p&otilde;hikooli ja g&uuml;mnaasiumi, mis tegutsevad &uuml;he asutusena) klassi&otilde;petaja, aine&otilde;petaja, logopeed, eripedagoog, kasvataja ja ringijuht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) class teachers, subject teachers, speech therapists, special education teachers, educators and hobby group leaders of nursery-primary schools, primary schools, basic schools and upper secondary schools (including upper secondary schools which have classes of basic school and basic schools and upper secondary schools which operate as one institution); </inglise>
<eesti>2) kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse &otilde;petaja; </eesti>
<inglise>2) teachers of vocational educational institutions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) huvialakooli &otilde;petaja, treener-&otilde;petaja, metoodik, klaverisaatja, kontsertmeister, ballettmeister, dirigent ja ringijuht. </eesti>
<inglise>3) teachers, coach-teachers, methodologists, piano accompanists, concertmasters, ballet masters, conductors and hobby group leaders of hobby schools. </inglise>
